article.headline: Wright St. 67, Youngstown St. 61
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio -- Todd Brown scored 20 points to lead Wright State to a 67-61 victory over Youngstown State on Thursday night. N'Gai Evans added 11 for the Raiders (13-8, 7-3 Horizon League). Tom Parks had 15 and Dallas Blocker had 12 for Youngstown (6-14, 3-7). Wright State led 28-26 at the half and was ahead 13 with just under 12 minutes left. But in the final minuts, the Raiders had to rally to perserve the win. A layup by the Penguins' DeAndre Mays with 56 seconds to go cut the Youngstown deficit to 3 at 62-59. But a layup by Evans, a free throw by Brown and two more by Will Graham let Wright State pull away again.
